<% @tab = "Home" %>

<div class="grid_12">
  <div style="padding-bottom:30px;">
    <div  style="padding-bottom:30px">
      <h2>Welcome</h2>
      <p><span style="font-weight:bold">Please Note:</span><br/>
      iMits is no longer accepting production data and has been replaced by GenTaR, a new tracking system.<br/>
      Please visit <a href="https://www.gentar.org/">GenTaR</a> for the most up to date production information.<br/>
      <span style="font-weight:bold">iMits is scheduled for retirement</span> and will be taken offline on <span style="font-weight:bold">2023-05-31</span>.<br/><br/><p><hr width="50%" align="left"/><br/>

      <p>Welcome to International Micro-Injection Tracking System. iMITS is the designated database for the planning of all IMPC mouse production,</br>
       as well as the central database to allow IMPC production centres to record the progress of mouse production, cre-excision and to summarise</br>
       the progress of phenotype data collection and transfer to the <a href="http://www.mousephenotype.org/">IMPC DCC</a>.</br></br>
       iMITS also stores all the mutation molecular structures made for the IKMC, as well as a catalog of all IKMC products.</br></br>
       All IMPC data (especially phenotyping data) can be found on <a href="http://www.mousephenotype.org/">the IMPC website</a></br></br>
       All IMPC-related queries should be addressed to <a href='mailto:mouse-helpdesk@ebi.ac.uk'>mouse-helpdesk@ebi.ac.uk</a></p>
    </div>

    <div style="padding-bottom:30px; border-bottom: 1px solid #bbb;">
      <h2>Getting data out of iMITS</h2>
      <p><span style="font-weight:bold">For web users</span>:<br/>
         You can directly browse all IMPC mouse production plans and progress, as well as IKMC ES Cell alleles on this website.
         <br/><br/>
         <span style="font-weight:bold">For developers</span>:<br/>
         Access to summary gene - level information and summary allele information can be obtained from our SOLR indices. instructions for querying that index can be found <a href='https://github.com/mpi2/imits/wiki/Accessing-Data-via-The-Solr-indicies'>here:</a>
         <br/><br/>
         Bulk access to all iMITS data can be obtained from the iMITS biomarts <a href='http://www.knockoutmouse.org/biomart/martview?VIRTUALSCHEMANAME=default&ATTRIBUTES=imits2.default.attributes.marker_symbol|imits2.default.attributes.mgi_accession_id|imits2.default.attributes.escell_clone|imits2.default.attributes.allele_symbol_superscript|imits2.default.attributes.production_centre|imits2.default.attributes.microinjection_status&FILTERS=&VISIBLEPANEL=mainpanel'>here:</a>
         <br/><br/>
        Bulk access to all IKMC allele data can be obtained from the targrep mart <a href='http://www.knockoutmouse.org/biomart/martview?VIRTUALSCHEMANAME=default&ATTRIBUTES=genes_targ_rep.default.attributes.pipeline|genes_targ_rep.default.attributes.ikmc_project_id|genes_targ_rep.default.attributes.mgi_accession_id|genes_targ_rep.default.attributes.targeting_vector|genes_targ_rep.default.attributes.escell_clone&FILTERS=&VISIBLEPANEL=mainpanel'>here:</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <table style="font-size: 85%">
